stylometry:
Transporation- has an origin and a destination. shows how a product travels from the origin to the destination. Example would be a short road trip where there are no stops made and you begin in one place and end in a different place.
Transshipment- has nodes, arcs, and flow. The nodes are places that have inflow and outflows such as warehouses. Arcs are the route the product takes when traveling from nodes to nodes. The flow is the quanitity that is traveling through the arcs. A example would be a manufacturing company, sending finished products to the warehouse who then ships it to all the retail stores.
